FBIS4-21738 "jptot014__l94038" JPRS-TOT-94-014-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 17 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA PERU Former MRTA Members Give Location of Yurimangas Common Grave Former MRTA Members Give Location of Yurimangas Common Grave PY2503180494 Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 17 Mar 94 p A10 PY2503180494 Lima EXPRESO Spanish BFN [Excerpt] Tarapoto -- It has been reported here that former Tupac Amaru Revolutionary Movement (MRTA) militants have made known the location of a common grave in Yurimangas that was dug by the movement's leaders. The clandestine cemetery is 40 km south of Yurimangas. It is believed to contain the remains of MRTA members who died in confrontations with the forces of order. It is also understood that the grave contains the victims of the MRTA's subversive insanity who, after being captured, were murdered without pity and their bodies thrown into the common grave. [passage omitted]
